## Q2 → Activate Support‑Entropy & Review

> **Question:** “Activate support entropy formulas and review.”

### Deterministic audit engine (ON)
- **Convert odds → probability**  
  - If odds < 0: \(p=\frac{|odds|}{|odds|+100}\)  
  - If odds > 0: \(p=\frac{100}{odds+100}\)

- **Leg entropy** (uncertainty per leg, in bits):  
  \[
  H(\text{leg}) = -\log_2\big(p(\text{leg})\big)
  \]

- **Parlay Entropy Score (PES)**  
  Sum leg entropies, then subtract **correlation credits** (support) or, equivalently, add **friction** if legs conflict:  
  \[
  \text{credit}_{ij}=\log_2\!\left(\frac{p(L_j\mid L_i)}{p(L_j)}\right),\quad
  PES=\sum_i H_i-\sum_{i<j}\text{credit}_{ij}
  \]

- **Support Entropy** (how much new uncertainty a “helper” leg adds to your target **T**):  
  \[
  SE(S\!\to\!T) = H(S\mid T) = -\log_2\!\big(p(S\mid T)\big)
  \]
  - Small \(SE\) ⇒ S is tightly implied by T (true support)  
  - Large \(SE\) ⇒ S is mostly independent or contradictory (decorative risk)

- **Support Integrity (SI)**:  
  \[
  SI(S\!\to\!T) = 1-\frac{H(S\mid T)}{H(S)}\in(-\infty,1]
  \]
  - ~+1 (excellent), ~0 (neutral), <0 (hurts your thesis)

**Audit thresholds**
- **Low entropy:** PES ≤ **1.5**  
- **Medium:** 1.5–**2.5**  
- **Flag:** PES > **2.5** **❗**

