## Quick Builder: Example Slips & PES Flags

> Not advice — an **audit lens** to understand compounding risk.

**Core duo (coherent):**  
- **Eagles ML** (example price −120 ⇒ \(p≈0.545\), \(H≈0.87\) bits)  
- **Chiefs Team Total Under 23.5** (−120 ⇒ \(p≈0.545\), \(H≈0.87\) bits)

**Independence sum:** ~**1.74** bits  
**Synergy credit (winner → opp. TT Under):** typically **+0.10–0.18** bits  
**PES:** ~**1.56–1.64** → **Low entropy** (clean causal chain)

**Add a “support” player leg (illustrative):**  
- **Kelce 6+ receptions** (e.g., +114 to +124 ⇒ \(p≈0.45–0.47\), \(H≈1.06–1.15\) bits)

- If \(p(\text{Kelce 6+} \mid \text{PHI ML ∧ KC TT U})\) is only marginally higher than baseline (or even slightly lower), then \(SE\) ≈ **1.05–1.10** bits and **SI** ≈ **0 to negative** → it **doesn’t** truly support the target.

**Three‑leg PES:** ~**2.7–2.9** → **❗ Flagged** (compounded uncertainty)

> Keep two‑leg builds unless your correlation math earns ≥ **0.25 bits** of total credit.

